  description="Physical-layer link types for quantum networks, ordered from most common and feasible to most speculative: standard single-mode fibre, hollow-core fibre, satellite, free-space optical, cryogenic microwave for superconducting QPUs, high-altitude platforms, and vacuum beam guide. Per-channel loss, reach, latency, and operational profile, grounded in ITU-T standards and the canonical experimental demonstrations."
